The 7th annual Global Entrepreneurship Summit (GES) took place at Stanford University in Silicon Valley, California, with a focus on promoting entrepreneurship as a driver for economic growth, social inclusion, and secure communities. The United States government announced new commitments to advance entrepreneurship globally, including programs to support clean energy entrepreneurs, women entrepreneurs, and entrepreneurs in developing countries. Private sector companies also made commitments to support the next generation of entrepreneurs through capital, mentorship, training, ecosystem support, and research. The summit showcased the global reach of entrepreneurship, with entrepreneurs and investors from 170 countries participating. India was announced as the host of the 2017 Global Entrepreneurship Summit.